description: There has been tragedy and triumph, despair and hope. For the past year, the rag-tag team thrown together under the banner of The Authority – accompanied by thousands of human refugees – has been off in deepest space, hoping to solve the mystery of The Carrier and perhaps bring home a cure for their shattered Earth. Now, after facing numerous unspeakable horrors, their long odyssey draws to its shattering, epic conclusion. The survivors are heading home – but what secret are they bringing with them?
name: Change, Not Die

description: There are many worlds in the universe outside of our own, connected by doors that are hidden to the eye. But if you chance upon those doors, you can be transported to a place where supple beauties reign supreme and all of your fantasies come alive. Should you pass through the doorways, be most careful, for the creatures you will meet can be as dangerous as they are beautiful. Many would die for a glimpse at those worlds-Miyuki would do anything to have them go away.
name: Vol. 1

description: Daughter of a brilliant professor, Asuna is a below-average student at Ecole du Ciel, where teachers and other students constantly belittle her. However, with the world spiraling toward war, Asuna's headed for a crash course in danger and love, as everyone prepares for combat...
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: The school closes to investigate the discovery of live ammunition in the simulator machines, and the students are given a much-needed break. But a secretive council governing the Ecole du Ciel school decides to send the students into space for further training. Later, Asuna returns home after hearing that her mother is ill--but it's all part of a scheme by the council, which seeks information about her father...
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: After fleeing from her mother's home, Asuna races to Zeon's National Defense University, where she finds Shinn, Emilu, and Erisia sightseeing. The gang decides to sneak into the University. But before they can get into too much trouble, combat breaks out in space, and an evacuation signal is given, returning the students to their school ship. Later, Asuna encounters a mysterious boy named Akira, who reveals that they were born and raised together--as experiments for a "superior hybrid breeding project." Meanwhile, Professor Forma discovers another shocking part of Asuna's past--the identity of her true father...
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: Asuna is combating Francis' Rick Dom. She must muscle through her emotions to survive this intense battle. Commander Toole discovers Asuna has quickly progressed through the Newtype project. Ecole will not stop now: the testing must continue, this time, in real combat.
name: Vol. 4

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: Shinn's death marks the destruction of the last of the Salamis, and Marie and her band of pirates return to their lair to celebrate their victory. But a shattered Asuna wants nothing more than revenge for the death of Shinn! When Marie offers her a place with the pirates, will Asuna accept--knowing the truth behind Shinn's death? Alliances are put to the test and Asuna better learn to muddle through the harsh realities of warfare if she is to survive in this next heart-stopping volume of École du Ciel!
name: Vol. 5

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: An entire year has passed since Shinn's death, and as Asuna continues to wrestle with the loss, Shinn's passing is only the beginning of a devastating chain reaction. Finally, the long build-up between A.E.U.G. and the Titans breaks into open warfare. But in order to reach victory, Marie must help Asuna get over her internal turmoil and resume her position as an ace Gundam pilot...
name: Vol. 6

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: Asuna and Jack Baird go into mock combat with Sophie in the back seat of Asuna's Nemo. Someone has sabotaged the Nemo's targeting OS, making Asuna unable to hit anything. Sophie can swap programs, but during that time the automated safety programs for both the Nemo and Baird's Gundam Mk-II will go down!
name: Vol. 7

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: Asuna has defied the odds, surviving countless attacks and dangerous situations. As the war continues and casualties mount, can she find the strength to go on? To make matters worse, Elisia's "readjustment" is complete along with her heightened abilities as a boosted human. She is immediately dispatched to finish off Asuna for good, but Asuna is ready for her, armed with a Newtype custom-made Gundam! Who will win in this Gundam battle of the fittest?
name: Vol. 8

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description: Though Asuna survived the explosion of her Rick Dias, the battle is far from over as Jack Baird and other A.E.U.G. pilots fight to hold Erisia off and buy Asuna time to get to the Le Cygne Gundam Unit. Asuna is able to drive off Erisia, but as one fight ends, another begins, as Captain Hank orders the Al Qasr to steal mobile armor being shipped to a colony for assembly. Can Asuna and the others stop this hostile hijacking in its tracks?
name: Vol. 9

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Ecole du Ciel

description:
1. Lunchboxes of Doom Featuring Flash Lightning

2. A city movie house after the last show.. Featuring The Raven

3. Ace McCoy, air-adventurer... Featuring Ace McCoy

4. Marvo the Magician and his monkey, Tito, on the highway to adventure Featuring Marvo the Magician

5. My daughter in the hands of those crooks.. Featuring Hap Hazard

6. X, FBI phantom and past master in the art.. Featuring X, the Phantom Fed

7. The Saddle Sleuth

8. With the invention of his Futuroscope..Featuring Whiz Wilson
name: Lunchboxes of Doom

description:
1. The Old Man of the Pyramids visits Lightning's city apartment Featuring Flash Lightning

2. The hour of midnight finds the Raven..Featuring The Raven

3. Ace McCoy, flying soldier of fortune, and his pal, Bill Regan...Featuring Ace McCoy

4. Marvo and Tito are driving along a road...Featuring Marvo the Magician

5. Rustling Tricks

6. X, a certain European power is trying hard..Featuring X, the Phantom Fed

7. Hey, Jones and O'Hara! Featuring Hap Hazard

8. Whiz sets his Futuroscope and lands..Featuring Whiz Wilson

Becomes Lightning Comics in next issue.
name: The Old Man of the Pyramids visits Lightning's city apartment

description: The One Year War between the Earth Federation and the Principality of Zeon has begun--and the newest Mobile Suits are tested for battle! Captain Matt Healy leads his team into dangerous territory as the leader of a Special Forces Experimental Unit. Ken Bederstadt is a Foreign Legion Lieutenant working in alliance with Zeon. These two heroes are trying to keep everyone alive...for tomorrow!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Lost War Chronicles

description: Following the fall of Odessa Base, the region falls under the overwhelming control of Federation forces. As the 03rd MS team conducts repairs on its Mobile Suits, a new batch of rookies trains to pilot the Federation's ever-expanding MS force for its next mission. 2nd Lt. Matt follows the order reluctantly, for fear of bringing raw rookies into combat--they must face off against Ken's Zeon expatriate unit. And so, Matt and Ken meet on the battlefield once again...
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam: Lost War Chronicles

description: After having finished a job at Research Colony Mendel, a mysterious mobile suit approaches the colony--likely with hostile intent. When Lowe Gear intercepts in the Red Frame, the pilot opens fire... and thus begins another exciting adventure set in the popular Gundam Seed universe! Mobile Suit Gundam SEED X Astray continues where Gundam Seed Astray R left off!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED X Astray

description: With the Dreadnought activated, Lowe's crew wins a game of chicken with Canard forcing him to retreat. With the ship still damaged, Canard returns with Hyperion to battle. Despite frail health, Prayer deploys in the Dreadnought to face Hyperion. Prayer must realize that a weapon of war can be used not just for killing people, but perhaps, to save lives as well. Will he learn the meaning of "ASTRAY?"
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED X Astray

description: A Handsome Stranger with a Dark Secret...Jae is your typical struggling artist, studying in Europe and dreaming of a successful painting career. Typical, that is, until her friend drops off a rather inebriated--though breathtakingly beautiful--young man at her apartment one evening. That night, Jae dreams that the stranger visits her in her room...and drinks her blood! But was it really all just a dream? Could this handsome creature truly be a blood-thirsty vampire? And if Jae actually considers his ominous proposition, will she be entering into a deal with the devil?
name: Prologue; Chapter One: Alter of Blood

description: Jae begins to learn more surprises about her tall, undead and handsome host Michael. Meanwhile, passion turns to competition, as Ken wants to get between Michael and Jae, vying for her sexual attention. And with the arrival of a new guest comes the naked truth about a loving obsession that turns into a blood lust.
name: Chapter Two: Mary

description: As Michael and Ken vie for Jae's affection, Eva makes a bold move to warn Jae to leave Michael's mansion. When Michael learns of this he throws a fit--but something holds him back from going into an uncontrollable. Afterward, Michael is unable to bring himself to drink from Jae. Is this vampire all bark and no bite?
name: Chapter 3: Possessions

description: In explosive revelations, friendships are pushed to the limit and lovers become bound until death do they part. When Ken reminisces about his first encounter with Michael, he discloses to Jae that he wanted something more from the vampire. Stunned, Jae has a secret or two to share...including a surprise about Eva that might knock Ken out!
name: Invitation To My Dream; Chapter Four: Memory

description: With Michael and Ken fighting for Jae's love, Jae contemplates leaving the mansion. She is drawn to Michael, both physically and emotionally, and temptation begins to take over Michael, too. When the heat intensifies, Jae reaches the point of no return with Michael. Has she really committed her heart and soul to this man?
name: Chapter Five: Freesia

description: Time and tragedy weave a tangled web of passion and loss as Jae gets a clearer picture of the one who made Michael into a vampire. All the while, various histories converge, and Adrian is the missing link that ties it all together. However, the next step in Jae and Michael's forbidden relationship begins to unfold...
name: Chapter Six: Vampire

description: Time is an unstoppable thief. Here in the mansion, a lifetime of deceit and pain is exposed to Jae. The truth about Adrian is revealed...but what will it mean for Ken? And as for Michael, the years of loneliness and emptiness have taken a toll. Can he allow himself to hope for something more with Jae, or will it be the end of everything? Find out in the final volume of Model!
name: Chapter Seven: Choice

description: Kokonose Mutsu, a descendant of the ogres who were banished from their own island by the mythical Japanese hero Momotaro centuries ago, is determined to reclaim his family's old glory. Fast-forward to present day: Kokonose is armed only with dubious powers, an adorable face, and a super-huge ego. He's all set to re-conquer his ancestors' home, which has been turned into a military school for ogre exterminators. You can be sure that these hardened soldiers are well prepared for any onslaught...but can they stop laughing at this ridiculous invader long enough to put up a fight? From Nanae Chrono, the creator of Peace Maker, Peace Maker Kurogane, and Vassalord, comes the hilarious adventures of a boy who just might make you die laughing!
name: Vol. 1

description: The ogres successfully invade the once impenetrable school grounds. For reasons even Kokonose can't fathom, the puppy-eyed, cute little ogres kidnap the Ninth Successor and his fellow classmates. Now it's time for Kokonose--and his monstrous powers--to let the little bugger have it. Will he return home a hero with an even bigger ego? Or will Senshiki have to come to the rescue once again?
name: Vol. 2

description: Kokonose and Kashii begin their "examination" to see if they can win the right to stay on Tougentou. But surviving in the woods and fighting off ogres turn out to be the least of their problems when an island invasion starts from a surprising source! Past friends become enemies, and with Momotaro himself in jeopardy, Kokonose is more than ready to step up in his place. But why is this all happening at now?!
name: Vol. 3

description: Crazy pirates! A student gone rogue! Momotaro himself in captivity! And a talking rabbit?! Kokonose is in serious trouble unless he can convince Kou-sensei to perform the mysterious and powerful soul-binding ritual...it's their one chance to defeat the Aza Ogre while the rest of the school forces try to hold off the invaders. But what are the consequences of Kou-sensei's decision? And what will happen to Kashii, who still can't transform, when he is taken hostage by the brutal invaders?
name: Vol. 4

description: Akira Nikaido is a typical slacker high school student who thinks he has a normal life--until a mysterious man called Shirogane appears and tells him to meet him at the school that night. He is skeptical but goes anyway...and gets attacked by a shadow monster! Shirogane convinces him that the balance between the human world and the shadow world has been distorted, and that Akira must become a shin--a creature of the shadow world--in order to help restore the balance. From KAILI SORANO comes a rebel without a cause--who has been given the ultimate supernatural power!
name: Vol. 1

description: The fact that Kengo, Aya and many other ordinary people are gaining the ability to see shins proves that the serious disruption between the worlds is getting worse. And now a serial killer is on the loose! As Shirogane and Akira pursue him, they not only discover that he may be a shin, but also that a sinister power from the shadow world is about to make its move...
name: Vol. 2

description: Akira demands answers, and for once Shirogane seems willing to provide them. He reveals that everything in the light world has a twin in the shadow world. A Shin's counterpart is called a "Rei." And as it happens, Akira is Shirogane's counterpart, destining him to become king of the Rei...
name: Vol. 3

description: Akira and friends confront Homurabi who, rather than being intimidated, is amused by their efforts. When Shirogane attempts to attack, he is easily deflected by Hiryu, one of Homurabi's five Shin "children." It may take every ounce of energy Shirogane has to take down these enemies, but what secrets is Homurabi hiding...?
name: Vol. 4
Nothing to fear but fear itself

description: Are you afraid of monsters? Well, they're afraid of you! Sulley and Mike work at Monsters, Inc., the biggest scream processing plant in Monstropolis. When one little child named Boo wanders into their world, it's the monsters who are scared silly. Thinking she is dangerous and toxic, Sulley and Mike do their best to return Boo to her bedroom, but there are some monstrous hurdles in their way. Treat yourself to the most entertaining manga of the year for Monster laughs and Monster fun that everyone will love...over and over again!
name: Vol. 1

description: In the 31st century, Earth is a long dead world; On the inhospitable mining world of Kanen, Ely, Rachel and Zak work as Ranger trouble-shooters.
Rickard captures Stark, drugs him and tries to convert him to the cause of the resistance; Rachel and Zak explore Herod's underworld.
Rachel and Zak are rescued by Beatle while searching the mines; Piel attempts to win Ely over to the side of the Old Lords; Baron Zara's thugs are out to kill all Rangers.

Ranz of the Marvots forges an alliance with the Rangers. Switchblade rounds up some heavy armor to improve the odds; The Rangers invade the upper levels of Herod to determine whether Baron Zara is the only enemy among the Alyvan.
Investigating a crashed ship, the Rangers are confronted by symbiotic creatures which take over the bodies of others to survive; They call themselves the O-Uahi, first masters of ancient Kanen.
name: What is the Price of Freedom?

description: Ely dreams he has journeyed to the Land of Dread; It is a deathless dimension where the Old Lords, the O-Uahi, rule; It is a hell which he has sent many others to; When he wakes up, one of the 'dream' demons is there.
name: What are Dreams Made of?

description: The O-Uahi invade Herod; Zak is absorbed and dies.
name: Herod Invaded

description: In a land submerged in a thousand years of fog, demons and nymphs do battle. Until one day, the fated meeting of sworn enemies unravels an intricate love story and hurls Ayaka, the daughter of the deity Reiki, into a voyage of discovery and maddening love. An original member of CLAMP, the world's best-selling manga studio, Tamayo Akiyama delivers an unforgettable fantasy adventure!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Mouryou Kiden: Legend of the Nymph

description: The invaders are destroyed, but so is the city of Herod.
name: Battle for Herod: Final Chapter

description: Ely and Rachel search in the wilderness for uncontaminated food; The rotting corpses of the aliens are releasing a madness-inducing plague which has turned most survivors against the Rangers; They manage to find Ely's lost sword of Kalichakra; They discover they can use this sword to open a dimensional gateway to escape the dying Kanen to another planet.
name: Out of the Ashes

description: Landing on a new world, our friends encounter the abandoned city of Yaxala-Kun and a powerful water-siren creature.
name: New Worlds for Old

description: Yaxala fills our crew in on how Lazafar destroyed their civilization; They are attacked by Lazafar's drones.
name: The Secret of Yaxala's Doom

description: Ely and crew head for Chernok to prevent Lazafar from destroying all life there; On the way, they meet some intergalactic traders; On Chernok, an anti-technology planet, they seek the high priest Vald.
name: Onward Through Deep Space

description: When Ayaka finds Kai, not everything is as it seems! Kai stabs Ayaka with "Muhyou no teki", the legendary flute of the Ogre Clan. But an enigmatic girl appears, with the same name as Kai's mother--Mikage--and intervenes. Ayaka and Kurama, with Mikage's cooperation, set their sights on Fuyo-Den, to try to find the meaning behind Kai's mysterious behavior!
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Mouryou Kiden: Legend of the Nymph

description: Ely and crew are captured by Priest Vald's enforcer on the planet Chernok; Rachel goes into a trance and draws the astral form of Zebvox to supply them with information.

Being pursued after killing Vald, our crew uses the blade to jump to another world; Lazafar reminisces more about his history; Our friends are captured by Liliathe, ruler of Shambaal; Liliathe wants to overthrow her father, Lazafar.

All the answers seem to lie in Fuyouden, so Ayaka travels there in order to find out the truth about her past, and to once again attempt to rescue her beloved Kai. As her comrades fall one by one, Ayaka is left alone to face the dark secret that is the foundation of her world. Things are not always what they seem--will Ayaka see the truth and still be able to save the love of her life? Find out in this final exciting volume fo Mouryou Kiden!
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: Mouryou Kiden: Legend of the Nymph

description: Rachel, Switchblade and what is left of Yaxala are rescued from Liliathe's experimentation labs by local rebels; Liliathe toys with Ely and confronts her father, Lazafar.
Ely and Lazafar disappear when Ely's sword touches Lazafar; Zebvox and Ribbt arrive with arms for Liliathe to use against Lazafar; The rebels obtain those weapons and begin their attack on Liliathe.
Back on a devastated planet Earth, Ely confronts Lazafar while everyone else battles his drones.
